  "prompt": "What are best prostate cancer websites?",
  "response": "When researching prostate cancer, it's important to refer to reputable sources that provide credible, up-to-date information. Here are some of the best websites for prostate cancer information:\n\n1. **American Cancer Society (cancer.org)**:\n   - Offers comprehensive information on prostate cancer, including causes, treatment options, statistics, and support resources.\n\n2. **National Cancer Institute (cancer.gov)**:\n   - Provides detailed information about prostate cancer, including research updates, clinical trials, and treatment guidelines.\n\n3. **Prostate Cancer Foundation (pcf.org)**:\n   - Dedicated to funding research for prostate cancer, this site offers information on recent advancements, support resources, and patient stories.\n\n4. **Cancer.net**:\n   - Managed by the American Society of Clinical Oncology (ASCO), it provides expert information about prostate cancer diagnosis, treatment, and living with cancer.\n\n5. **Urology Care Foundation (urologyhealth.org)**:\n   - Includes information on prostate health, prostate cancer, treatment options, and patient support resources.\n\n6. **WebMD (webmd.com)**:\n   - Offers a wealth of information on prostate cancer, including symptoms, treatments, and patient care tips, reviewed by medical experts.\n\n7. **Mayo Clinic (mayoclinic.org)**:\n   - Provides detailed information on prostate cancer, its diagnosis, treatment, and management, from a leading medical institution.\n\n8. **Johns Hopkins Medicine (hopkinsmedicine.org)**:\n   - Offers insights from one of the leading medical research centers, including information on prostate cancer detection, treatment, and ongoing research.\n\n9. **Prostate Cancer UK (prostatecanceruk.org)**:\n   - Focuses on prostate cancer awareness, education, and support in the UK, offering resources for both patients and healthcare providers.\n\n10. **National Comprehensive Cancer Network (NCCN) (nccn.org)**:\n   - Provides guidelines for cancer care, including prostate cancer, developed by expert providers.\n\nWhen visiting these websites, it's always good to look for information authored or reviewed by medical professionals and up-to-date with the latest research and guidelines.",
